    • Constructor Detail

      • Model

        public Model(String prefix,
             String displayId,
             String version,
             URI source,
             URI language,
             URI framework)
      throws SBOLValidationException
        Creates a Model instance with the given arguments.

        If the given prefix does not end with one of the following delimiters: "/", ":", or "#", then "/" is appended to the end of it.

        This method requires the given prefix, displayId, and version are not null and valid.

        A Model instance is created with a compliant URI. This URI is composed from the given prefix, the given displayId, and version. The display ID, persistent identity, and version fields of this instance are then set accordingly.

        Parameters:
        prefix -
        displayId -
        version -
        source -
        language -
        framework -
        Throws:
        SBOLValidationException - if the defaultURIprefix is null
        SBOLValidationException - if the given URIprefix is null
        SBOLValidationException - if the given URIprefix is non-compliant
        SBOLValidationException - if the given displayId is invalid
        SBOLValidationException - if the given version is invalid

        public void setSource(URI source)

        Sets the source property to the given argument.

        If this Model object belongs to an SBOLDocument instance, then the SBOLDcouement instance is checked for compliance first. Only a compliant SBOLDocument instance is allowed to be edited.

        Parameters:
        source - a URI reference to the source file for a model.
        Throws:
        SBOLValidationException - if the associated SBOLDocument is not compliant.
        SBOLValidationException - if the given source argument is null
